        "text": {
          "content": "2\n*\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0001\u0000\u0000\u0000\u0002\u0000\u0000\u0001jGo inside base1. out1 is an Out POP that is ued to wire POPs from inside the component to nodes in its parent component, in this case null1.\n\nWhen you rollover the output connector, of base1 you see a custom label, \"Nice Geonmetry\", set with the IOut POP's Label parameter. \n\nThe selec POP gets the same data but it's assoming the name of the Output POP is out1.",
